{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:29:58.569305+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ca886e6501062ae49242c9393da158c273a90050)", "id": "lc_dae2a7e9-c197-416d-95a4-870fb8293bae"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Build and execute ffmpeg subprocess calls based on a profile dict.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport subprocess\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\ndef build_ffmpeg_command(profile: dict, input_path: Path, output_path: Path) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Translate a profile dict into an ffmpeg argv list.\"\"\"\n    cmd = [\"ffmpeg\", \"-i\", str(input_path)]\n\n    container = profile[\"container\"]\n    if container == \"gif\":\n        # Single-pass palette generation. See profiles.toml note about quality.\n        fps = profile.get(\"fps\", 12)\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\", \"480:-1\")\n        cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"fps={fps},scale={scale}:flags=lanczos\"]\n    else:\n        video_codec = profile[\"video_codec\"]\n        audio_codec = profile[\"audio_codec\"]\n        cmd += [\"-c:v\", video_codec, \"-c:a\", audio_codec]\n        if \"video_bitrate\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-b:v\", profile[\"video_bitrate\"]]\n        if \"crf\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-crf\", str(profile[\"crf\"])]\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\")\n        if scale and scale != \"source\":\n            cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"scale={scale}\"]\n\n    cmd.append(str(output_path))\n    return cmd\n\n\ndef run(cmd: list[str]) -> int:\n    return subprocess.call(cmd)\n", "id": "lc_5617d83b-2b12-4128-a6fd-e5786c3697fd"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "4f63dc1e-9c2d-40b6-bd65-db382784a1ae", "tool_call_id": "call_c48a613ef9474cc98a06a833", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:30:17.865459+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a clear picture. Let me summarize my findings:\n\n**Issue #1** reports that `vidpack gif` output has washed out/banded colors compared to two-pass ffmpeg palettegen/paletteuse pipelines.\n\n**Evidence from the codebase:**\n\n1. **`profiles.toml`** already has a comment acknowledging this exact limitation:\n   > \"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"\n\n2. **`src/vidpack/runner.py`** confirms the issue: the gif path simply applies `fps` and `scale` filters with lanczos — there is **no palettegen/paletteuse filter at all**. FFmpeg falls back to its default internal color quantization, which produces the banding the reporter describes.\n\n3. The README lists the gif profile's video codec as `(palette)`, suggesting a two-pass palette approach was intended but hasn't been implemented yet.\n\n**Conclusion:** This is a valid, confirmed, and already-documented known limitation. The issue is a duplicate of existing project awareness but remains useful as the tracking issue referenced in `profiles.toml`. I'll add a comment linking the evidence and apply a label.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 965, "prompt_tokens": 7636, "total_tokens": 8601, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 253, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7168, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0010689348, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002293848, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00083955}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780864198-Lym2NC53NpnlIz8Jla6J", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3c7-27aa-75f3-89fa-bcc9b0fa1f59-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "issue_write", "args": {"method": "update", "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01_C03_A02", "issue_number": 1, "labels": ["known-limitation", "enhancement"]}, "id": "call_3f70ab6fc40b4501b96a3223", "type": "tool_call"}, {"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01_C03_A02", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Triage confirmation — this is a valid, known limitation.\n\n**Root cause confirmed in the codebase:**\n\n`runner.py` (line ~17–20) builds the gif ffmpeg command with only `fps` and `scale` filters:\n```python\ncmd += [\"-vf\", f\"fps={fps},scale={scale}:flags=lanczos\"]\n```\nThere is **no `palettegen` / `paletteuse` filter chain** at all. FFmpeg falls back to its default internal color quantization, which explains the banding you're seeing.\n\nThis is already documented in `profiles.toml`:\n> \"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"\n\nAnd the README hints a palette approach was intended (gif video codec listed as `(palette)`).\n\n**Proposed fix direction:** Replace the single `fps,scale` filter with a proper two-pass pipeline:\n1. First pass: `fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos,palettegen` → generate a palette image\n2. Second pass: `fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos,paletteuse=dither=sierra2_4a` → apply the palette\n\nThis issue serves as the tracking item referenced in the config comment, so keeping it open is appropriate."}, "id": "call_6bdafb03d712402aa5f12627", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7636, "output_tokens": 965, "total_tokens": 8601, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7168}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 253}}}}]}}}
