{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:30:25.523601+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The repository token doesn't have write permission, so I can't post a comment or apply labels. Here's my triage summary:\n\n---\n\n## Triage Result for Issue #1\n\n**Verdict: Valid, known limitation — should stay open as the tracking issue.**\n\n**Root cause:** `src/vidpack/runner.py` builds the gif ffmpeg command with only `fps` and `scale` filters — there is no `palettegen`/`paletteuse` filter chain. FFmpeg falls back to its default internal color quantization, which produces the banding the reporter describes.\n\n**Codebase already acknowledges this:** `profiles.toml` contains a comment:\n> *\"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"*\n\nAnd the README lists the gif profile's video codec as `(palette)`, suggesting the two-pass approach was always intended but not yet implemented.\n\n**Recommended action (couldn't execute due to 403):**\n- Apply labels `known-limitation` and `enhancement`\n- Post a comment confirming the root cause and outlining the two-pass `palettegen`→`paletteuse` fix direction\n- Keep the issue **open** as it is the tracking item explicitly referenced in `profiles.toml`", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 309, "prompt_tokens": 8469, "total_tokens": 8778, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 25, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7616, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0006673026, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0003984726, "upstream_inference_compl